The way this mod works is the cross is created and is treated as persistent because of these entries you are going to move over. 

Simply paste this into your types.xml file while maintaining the format of it, and adjust the lifetime values, in seconds, as you wish. The current defaults I have set up is 5 minutes for any crosses created on the coast, and 25 minutes for all others. These will persist through server restarts too!

Not A Banana#9930 on discord for any inquiries 

UPDATE: Previously "DiedOnCoastCross" was determined by specific x and y coordinates to determine if you were on the coast. This meant the mod only really worked correctly on Chernarus. Now, I have moved to player survived time. If you die within first 30 minutes of your life, the coast cross will spawn
with the low lifetime value. Over 30 minutes, normal cross. 
    <type name="GraveCross">
        <lifetime>1500</lifetime>
        <flags count_in_cargo="0" count_in_hoarder="0" count_in_map="1" count_in_player="0" crafted="1" deloot="0"/>
    </type>	
	<type name="DiedOnCoastCross">
        <lifetime>300</lifetime>
        <flags count_in_cargo="0" count_in_hoarder="0" count_in_map="1" count_in_player="0" crafted="1" deloot="0"/>
    </type>	